-- Bomb in Lebanon’s Bekaa Injures Hezbollah Members, LBC Reports
-- B y   D o n n a   A b u - N a s r
-- 2013-07-16T14:20:15Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-07-16/bomb-in-lebanon-s-bekaa-injures-hezbollah-members-lbc-reports.html
A bomb exploded in Lebanon’s eastern
Bekaa Valley today, injuring members of the Iranian-backed
Hezbollah group who were in a car headed to the border with
 Syria , LBC TV said.  The official National News Agency said two people were
injured in the blast in the Masnaa region. Army troops cordoned
off the area, according to footage aired by LBC.  Hezbollah has been fighting alongside troops loyal to
Syrian President Bashar al-Assad. Syrian rebels have said they
will target the group in Lebanon. On July 9, a car bomb exploded
in the Hezbollah stronghold of Bir el-Abed in southern  Beirut ,
injuring 53 people.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Donna Abu-Nasr in Beirut at 
 dabunasr@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
